51//! Abstract base class for convention objects
52/*!
53 \ingroup configuration
54 */
55class Convention : public XMLSerializable {
56public:
57 //! Supported convention types
58 enum class Type {
59 Zero,
60 Deposit,
61 Future,
62 FRA,
63 OIS,
64 Swap,
65 AverageOIS,
66 TenorBasisSwap,
67 TenorBasisTwoSwap,
68 BMABasisSwap,
69 FX,
70 CrossCcyBasis,
71 CrossCcyFixFloat,
72 CDS,
73 IborIndex,
74 OvernightIndex,
75 SwapIndex,
76 ZeroInflationIndex,
77 InflationSwap,
78 SecuritySpread,
79 CMSSpreadOption,
80 CommodityForward,
81 CommodityFuture,
82 FxOption,
83 BondYield
84 };
85
86 //! Default destructor
87 virtual ~Convention() {}
88
89 //! \name Inspectors
90 //@{
91 const string& id() const { return id_; }
92 Type type() const { return type_; }
93 //@}
94
95 //! \name convention interface definition
96 //@{
97 virtual void build() = 0;
98 //@}
99
100protected:
101 Convention() {}
102 Convention(const string& id, Type type);
103 Type type_;
104 string id_;
105};
106
107//! Repository for currency dependent market conventions
108/*!
109 \ingroup market
110*/
111class Conventions : public XMLSerializable {
112public:
113 //! Default constructor
114 Conventions() {}
115
116 /*! Returns the convention if found and throws if not */
117 boost::shared_ptr<Convention> get(const string& id) const;
118
119 /*! Get a convention with the given \p id and \p type. If no convention of the given \p type with the given \p id
120 is found, the first element of the returned pair is \c false and the second element is a \c nullptr. If a
121 convention is found, the first element of the returned pair is \c true and the second element holds the
122 convention.
123 */
124 std::pair<bool, boost::shared_ptr<Convention>> get(const std::string& id, const Convention::Type& type) const;
125
126 /*! Get all conventions of a given type */
127 std::set<boost::shared_ptr<Convention>> get(const Convention::Type& type) const;
128
129 /*! Find a convention for an FX pair */
130 boost::shared_ptr<Convention> getFxConvention(const string& ccy1, const string& ccy2) const;
131
132 //! Checks if we have a convention with the given \p id
133 bool has(const std::string& id) const;
134
135 //! Checks if we have a convention with the given \p id and \p type
136 bool has(const std::string& id, const Convention::Type& type) const;
137
138 /*! Clear all conventions */
139 void clear();
140
141 /*! Add a convention. This will overwrite an existing convention
142 with the same id */
143 void add(const boost::shared_ptr<Convention>& convention);
144
145 //! \name Serialisation
146 //@{0
147 virtual void fromXML(XMLNode* node) override;
148 virtual XMLNode* toXML(XMLDocument& doc) override;
149 //@}
150
151private:
152 map<string, boost::shared_ptr<Convention>> data_;
153 mutable boost::shared_mutex mutex_;
154};
155
156//! Singleton to hold conventions
157//
158class InstrumentConventions : public QuantLib::Singleton<InstrumentConventions, std::integral_constant<bool, true>> {
159 friend class QuantLib::Singleton<InstrumentConventions, std::integral_constant<bool, true>>;
160
161private:
162 // may be empty but never uninitialised
163 InstrumentConventions() : conventions_(boost::make_shared<ore::data::Conventions>()) {}
164
165 boost::shared_ptr<ore::data::Conventions> conventions_;
166 mutable boost::shared_mutex mutex_;
167
168public:
169 const boost::shared_ptr<ore::data::Conventions>& conventions() const {
170 boost::shared_lock<boost::shared_mutex> lock(mutex_);
171 return conventions_;
172 }
173 void setConventions(const boost::shared_ptr<ore::data::Conventions>& conventions) {
174 boost::unique_lock<boost::shared_mutex> lock(mutex_);
175 conventions_ = conventions;
176 }
177};

1342 : type_(OptionAnchorType::DayOfMonth), daysBefore_(""), expiryDay_(expiryDay.dayOfMonth_), nth_(""),
